            <scopecontent id="aspace_3d8247e499b80e680a647f5a490b875f">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Correspondence of Yale School of Medicine student members of the Harvey Cushing Chapter of AIMS, especially Lewis P. Rowland (YSM 1948 ) and Ruth Leyendecker (Cort) (YSM, 1951). Most of the correspondence is with potential invited speakers. They included Yale faculy members such as Ashley Oughterson and C.E.-A. Winslow, as well as such out-of-town physicians as Michael M. Davis, Chairman of the Committee on Research in Medical Economics, and Montague Cobb, Howard University.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
