            <scopecontent id="aspace_24270dbdce1416cfcb6bdc79022d85f9">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The National Society for Medical Research advocated for the use of animals in medical research and counteracted anti-vivisection movements. The Society reached out to members of AIMS. Included is a mimeograph letter from Executive Secretary Ralph Rohweder to Ruth Leyendecker at Yale, and various other publications of the Society.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
